posts.title: Patriots
posts.content:
As the name of the site reaches four years old. We owe it to everyone here a huge thanks and congratulations. You successfully said “fuck you” to a hundred years of establishment. Then you did it again and now for a third time you have achieved greatness.

I won’t lie and say the past four years have been awesome. Some of you were arrested four years ago others questioned by the police and feds for giving a shit about your way of life. Personally my life has changed completely since patriots day. This site has also changed, for four years it has been bad news and what has Biden done to screw our lives up. While we’ll continue to highlight terrible liberal policies and practices we now have the opportunity and privilege to highlight the wins that you helped intact by making Trump your president.

I expect great things to come from this administration.

Economic Growth and Jobs: Trump has historically prioritized economic policies aimed at reducing regulations, lowering taxes, and promoting job creation, especially in manufacturing and energy.

Immigration Reform: Trump has been vocal about strengthening border security and reforming the immigration system. His administration previously introduced strict policies on illegal immigration, and we should expect a similar emphasis on border control.

America First Foreign Policy: Trump is known for his “America First” foreign policy, emphasizing a reduction in military commitments abroad, renegotiating trade deals, and focusing on protecting U.S. interests in global affairs. His stance on reducing international entanglements might continue, with an emphasis on strengthening relationships with allies while challenging adversaries like China.

Law and Order: Trump has championed a “law and order” stance, positioning himself as a defender of the police and criminal justice system. A second term could see continued efforts to support law enforcement agencies and oppose movements to defund the police.

Judicial Appointments: Trump’s influence over the federal judiciary, particularly his appointment of conservative judges to federal courts, has been a significant legacy. He’ll continue to appoint judges who align with conservative values, further shifting the judicial landscape.

Manifest America: At one point in history America and Monroe declared to the world that this hemisphere was ours. While it’s unclear how Canada Greenland Panama and the rest of the continent stands to navigate through this it’ll be exciting to watch.

Every single executive order will be glorified and every deal to make America great will be plastered on this site. We are here now and we won’t be going anywhere.

Finally thanks frens, let’s make America great
